<p><FONT CLASS=Title3><b>1. <a name="Q1">What is Mobhunter?</a></b></font>

<p><FONT CLASS=Title4>Mobhunter is a news site dedicated to the game of EverQuest and issues that affect its players. If you don't play EverQuest and aren't interested in the game, you're at the wrong site and may want to try a different search engine.</font>

<p><FONT CLASS=Title4>The thing that hopefully differentiates Mobhunter from other news sites is that we dig deeper and examine the larger issues behind the stories. We tend to focus on major game events and keep a close eye on the actions taken by Verant and its staff, reporting on the implications of the company's actions (or lack thereof) to the playerbase. While we are supportive and appreciative of the great game Verant has provided for us, we aren't afraid to hold them accountable for their mistakes.</font>

<p><FONT CLASS=Title4>We do not post articles about trade bazaars or naked troll races. Our focus is not on small-scale events that affect only one server, but on major incidents that touch the playerbase as a whole. We pass this information along in a manner that is hopefully humorous, thought provoking, and enjoyable to read.</font>

<p><FONT CLASS=Title4>Our readers are encouraged to submit news stories and editorials to us. We will post stories and credit authors who provide us with original news and perspectives that fit our general writing style.</font>
